user.biography: WHERE ANIMALS COME FIRST ❤️ Brolga & Tahnee - wildlife carers 🦘We rescue & raise orphaned kangaroos. Meet our roos on tour. Home of Kangaroo Dundee 🦘

node.text:
Thanks for all your kindness to us Aussies. Please visit us. We can’t wait to see you 🧡

Repost: @australia ❤️
We want to send our mates around the world a big thank you for all your love and support. We hope you will come visit soon!

node.text: Welcome darling orphan Baby, who we picked up yesterday from rescuer Erin. Baby is a good friend for Cam. They are about the same size, so are perfect together. 💖🧡

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Kangaroo Sanctuary 🦘 in Arrernte Country with @shannonpetersonn. May be an image of 1 person, standing, animal and outdoors.

node.text:
On our sunset tour 🦘😍
Repost @shannonpetersonn 
My lifelong dream of holding a joey has come true 🦘 And I got to hold TWO! They were so cute and snuggly 🥰 one of my favorite days ever

node.text: Tiny sweet orphan Cam loves being snuggled between my teddy bear I had as a baby and quokka while the bigger joeys are out for a hop. Cam came to us very sick a few days ago. He is recovering well. 💖

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Kangaroo Sanctuary 🦘 in Arrernte Country. May be an image of 1 person, animal and outdoors.

node.text: Sweet little orphan Cam arrived Wednesday. He loves being snuggled between new sister Elizabeth and brother Pip. Grow strong little one. 💖

node.text: Our BBC documentary Kangaroo Dundee and other Animals is currently showing on BBC2 Natural World. 🦘🧡

node.text: Hi Aussies 🇦🇺 Kangaroo Dundee is available to stream on 9Now. This doco is about our beautiful rescue kangaroos. Made by BBC UK and Natural World, our doco has been shown in over 35 countries. We hope you enjoy this series (which is one of 3 series made a few years ago). 🧡

Can you believe this gorgeous mum and baby are part of the kangaroo (macropod) family. 😍 This is a Black-Footed Rock Wallaby we watched up close today at our local Olive Pink Botanic Garden.
